Collection:

A Collection is a group of objects.

Arrays also is a basic collection only but drawbacks are:

i) Homogenous

ii) 



Iterable is extended by Collection interface.


Collection contains List , Queue , Set

List: ArrayList, LinkedList, vector, Stack

Queue: PriorityQueue, Dequeue


Map: Map does not come in Iterable.. we can't iterate a map.. directly we can't use iterator it to iterate a map.

Convert it to a set or list like that an then iterate


In Collections, there are three things there:

1.Collection

2. Collection Interface

3. Collection class in Util class



Some classes are there from Java version 1 itself.. Those are called as Legacy classes.

1. Vector , Stack , HashTable are all legacy classes.



