List:

List is an Interface

List Interface methods:


ArrayList:
  It's an Implementation class to List Interface

  -> collection of objects

  -> Duplicates allowed

  -> Maintains Insertion order

  -> Used if our frequent operation is retrieval operation as it implements Random..  Interface

   ->The Integer, String or whatever we are adding are not like primitive int etc..  They are objects... bcoz it is collection of Objects

   If we add an integer, It is Wrapped by Integer class.


  -> We can't put System.out.println(alist[])... 

    Bcoz, it's dynamic Resizable array...also, It is a class. so, classname. methodname we should put



Comparable - used for only one level of Sorting

Comparator is used when we have many levels of sorting. When we should do branch wise, then name, then salary wise... comparable can't be used...then name wise you put



LinkedList:


Node:

two parts: data and address of another node .. which is next of type Node


head=null -> no linked list



offerLast: insert at last place



Double -ended queue: 2 front , 2 back are there


We don't use search in linkedlist operation...


It's is best choice for frequent insertion and deletion... bcoz not continuous memory



Vector:

- Has Synchronization

- Multithreads will be there

- Many threads will be there... it makes other threads wait and make it complete the performing thread.. It puts lock to all..

This condition is called Race condition.



HashSet:

Hashing:
 For Search operation, we will go here

  
We store the data in HashTable... we store using Hash function

Let there be table of size 10. 45%10 =5.. 72%10=2





//duplicate values are not allowed
 -> but it will not show any error
-> it gets replaced with the same value


-> no random access... so, get method won't work

//Normal for loop not possible.. bcoz no indexing is there..

so the advanced for loop is possible


Linked Hash Set: Linked List + Hash Table

Actually, when 45, 75 are there... we will go to the next index there... linear probing we do


But, when we form a linked list and store it on the same row, it is called Linked HashSet.


TreeSet: TreeSet maintains the order

so, when you give homogenous data, it will sort as usual

But, when you give heterogenous data, it does n't know by what means , it should compare..


Tree Set uses Red-Black tree

This tree uses BST logic




